There are two candidate CDs. 
 The positive CD has the following information: Back in Black — cohesive late‑70s hard‑rock: midrange‑forward crunchy guitars, riff‑led 3–5 minute songs, tight driving drums, gravelly vocals; analog‑rooted mixes and light, transient‑preserving mastering deliver muscular low‑mid, immediate live feel and consistent sequencing that rewards repeat, attentive listening over glossy polish.. 
